DURBAN - The ANC Youth League in KwaZulu-Natal says it won't apologise to the Active Citizens Movement, for disrupting Ahmed Kathrada s memorial service in Durban.The group had asked the league to issue an apology by 16:00 Saturday afternoon.Instead, the league has requested an urgent meeting with the Active Citizens Movement, to discuss the matter.WATCH: Ahmed Kathrada memorial in Durbanit wants an opportunity to explain its side of the story, and insists it won't apologise as it believes the disruption was justifiable.The league heckled ANC treasurer general Zweli Mkhize and former finance minister Pravin Gordhan when they spoke at the memorial.The movement says it will speak to its lawyers before commenting.WATCH: ANCYL disrupt Kathrada Memorial in Durban eNCA